維生素D有很多種不同的形式存在。兩種最主要的維生素D種類分別是維生素D<sub>2</sub>（[[麥角鈣化醇|麥角鈣化醇]]）和維生素D<sub>3</sub>（[[膽鈣化醇|膽鈣化醇]]），它們統稱為鈣化醇。1932年，研究人員闡明了維生素D<sub>2</sub>的結構，而人們於1936年發現了維生素D<sub>3</sub>，並發現它可以由7-脫氫膽固醇經紫外線照射轉化而成<ref>[http://vitamind.ucr.edu/history.html History of Vitamin D] {{Wayback|url=http://vitamind.ucr.edu/history.html |date=20111128033458 }} University of California, Riverside, Vitamin D Workshop.</ref>。沒有下標的是涵蓋所有維生素D，指D<sub>2</sub>或D<sub>3</sub>或是兩者，這些統稱為鈣化醇<ref>''Dorland's Illustrated Medical Dictionary'', under Vitamin (Table of Vitamins)</ref>。維生素D<sub>2</sub>的化學特徵是在1931年獲證明，維生素D<sub>3</sub>的化學結構於1935年建立，並證明是紫外線照射7-脫氫膽固醇而產生的<ref name="River">[http://vitamind.ucr.edu/about.html About Vitamin D] {{Wayback|url=http://vitamind.ucr.edu/about.html |date=20111115060853 }} Including Sections: History, Nutrition, Chemistry, Biochemistry, and Diseases. University of California Riverside</ref>。從化學結構上來說，維他命D都屬於開環甾體化合物，也就是甾體激素的一個環狀結構打開了<ref name="River"/>，維生素D<sub>2</sub>與維生素D<sub>3</sub>結構的不同之處在於其側鏈，維生素D<sub>2</sub>的22和23位碳之間是雙鍵，而且在24位碳上多了一個甲基；維生素D<sub>3</sub>（膽鈣化醇）可以由其前體7-脫氫膽固醇經過紫外線照射變構形成，只要讓皮膚暴露於充足的紫外光下即可以自然產生足夠維生素D<sub>3</sub>的分量，奶製品廠家通常把牛奶置於紫外線光下，以強化其中的維生素D<sub>3</sub>。

化學上，各種形式的維他命D都是{{le|開環甾體|secosteroid}}，即[[類固醇|類固醇]]，類固醇環的其中之一個鍵被破壞<ref name="River"/>。維他命D<sub>2</sub>和維他命D<sub>3</sub>之間的結構差異在於D<sub>2</sub>在碳22和23之間包含著一個[[側鏈|側鏈]]，以及在碳24上有一個[[甲基|甲基]]。

維他命D<sub>2</sub>是麥角固醇的衍生物，麥角固醇之所以以「麥角」命名，因為它是從一種名為[[麥角菌|麥角菌]]的[[真菌|真菌]]細胞膜上找到的固醇。麥角固醇同時也可以由浮游生物、無脊椎動物以及其他真菌合成。麥角固醇一經合成，在紫外線照射下就可以轉化為麥角鈣化醇，陸地動物和脊椎動物中的維他命D<sub>2</sub>，由於牠們體內不能合成麥角固醇，但能夠合成維他命D<sub>3</sub><ref name=holick2011>{{cite journal | author=Holick MF, Binkley NC, Bischoff-Ferrari HA, Gordon CM, Hanley DA, Heaney RP, Murad MH, Weaver CM| title = Evaluation, treatment, and prevention of vitamin D deficiency: an Endocrine Society clinical practice guideline |journal = J Clin Endocrinol Metab| date = 2011-06-06| pmid = 21646368| doi=10.1210/jc.2011-0385 | volume=96 | issue=7 | pages=1911–30}}</ref>，但關於人類只服用維他命D<sub>2</sub>能否代替維他命D<sub>3</sub>攝入的討論，當中的爭論還是很激烈<ref name="pmid17023693">{{cite journal| author = Houghton LA, Vieth R| title = The case against ergocalciferol (vitamin D<sub>2</sub>) as a vitamin supplement| journal = [[The_American_Journal_of_Clinical_Nutrition|The American Journal of Clinical Nutrition]]| volume = 84| issue = 4| pages = 694–7| pmid = 17023693| url = http://www.ajcn.org/content/84/4/694.full.pdf| date = October 2006| access-date = 2012-01-02| archive-date = 2012-07-03| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120703210542/http://www.ajcn.org/content/84/4/694.full.pdf| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="Holick Biancuzzo Chen Klein 2008 pp. 677–681">{{cite journal | last=Holick | first=Michael F. | last2=Biancuzzo | first2=Rachael M. | last3=Chen | first3=Tai C. | last4=Klein | first4=Ellen K. | last5=Young | first5=Azzie | last6=Bibuld | first6=Douglass | last7=Reitz | first7=Richard | last8=Salameh | first8=Wael | last9=Ameri | first9=Allen | last10=Tannenbaum | first10=Andrew D. | title=Vitamin D2Is as Effective as Vitamin D3in Maintaining Circulating Concentrations of 25-Hydroxyvitamin D | journal=The Journal of Clinical Endocrinology & Metabolism | publisher=The Endocrine Society | volume=93 | issue=3 | year=2008 | issn=0021-972X | doi=10.1210/jc.2007-2308 | pages=677–681}}</ref>。

== 生物學 ==
活性維他命D代謝物骨化三醇透過跟主要位於靶細胞的[[細胞核|細胞核]]中的{{le|維他命D受體（VDR）|Vitamin D receptor}}結合來介導其生物學作用<ref name="River" />。骨化三醇與VDR的結合使VDR可以作為[[轉錄因子|轉錄因子]]來調節轉運蛋白的[[基因表達|基因表達]]（如{{le|TRPV6|TRPV6}}和[[鈣合蛋白|鈣合蛋白]]），它們參與腸道中鈣質的吸收<ref name=Bouillon2003>{{cite journal | vauthors = Bouillon R, Van Cromphaut S, Carmeliet G | title = Intestinal calcium absorption: Molecular vitamin D mediated mechanisms | journal = Journal of Cellular Biochemistry | volume = 88 | issue = 2 | pages = 332–9 | date = February 2003 | pmid = 12520535 | doi = 10.1002/jcb.10360 }}</ref>。維他命D受體屬於{{le|類固醇／甲狀腺激素受體|Steroid hormone receptor}}的[[核受體|核受體]]超級家族，以及VDR表現於大多數[[器官|器官]]的細胞中，包括[[腦|腦]]、[[心臟|心臟]]、[[皮膚|皮膚]]、[[生殖腺|生殖腺]]、[[前列腺|前列腺]]和[[乳房|乳房]]。

在小腸、骨骼、腎臟及甲狀旁腺細胞的VDR激活導致血液中鈣和磷的水平得以維持（在甲狀旁腺激素和[[降鈣素|降鈣素]]的輔助下），並維持了骨骼含量<ref name="Holick 2004">{{cite journal | vauthors = Holick MF | title = Sunlight and vitamin D for bone health and prevention of autoimmune diseases, cancers, and cardiovascular disease | journal = The American Journal of Clinical Nutrition | volume = 80 | issue = 6 Suppl | pages = 1678S–88S | date = December 2004 | pmid = 15585788 | doi = 10.1093/ajcn/80.6.1678S | doi-access = free }}</ref>。

維他命D的最重要作用之一是透過促進腸道內的{{le|鈣代謝|Calcium metabolism}}以維持骨骼中鈣質的平衡，並通過增加[[破骨細胞|破骨細胞]]的數量和保持[[成骨作用|成骨作用]]中鈣和磷酸鹽水平以促進{{le|骨吸收|Bone resorption}}，並讓甲狀旁腺激素的正常運作以維持血清中鈣的水平。[[維生素D缺乏症|維他命D缺乏症]]會導致骨骼礦物質密度降低，並由於缺乏維他命D會改變人體中的礦物質代謝，導致骨密度降低（[[骨質疏鬆症|骨質疏鬆症]]）或[[骨折|骨折]]風險的增加<ref name="Bell">{{cite journal | vauthors = Bell TD, Demay MB, Burnett-Bowie SA | title = The biology and pathology of vitamin D control in bone | journal = Journal of Cellular Biochemistry | volume = 111 | issue = 1 | pages = 7–13 | date = September 2010 | pmid = 20506379 | pmc = 4020510 | doi = 10.1002/jcb.22661 }}</ref>。因此，維他命D通過作為骨吸收中有效刺激物的作用，這對{{le|骨骼重塑|Bone remodeling}}也至關重要<ref name=Bell/>。

VDR調節[[細胞增殖|細胞增殖]]和[[細胞分化|細胞分化]]。維他命D也影響免疫系統，而VDR在幾種[[白血球|白血球]]中表達，包括[[单核细胞|單核白血球]]和活化的[[T細胞|T細胞]]和[[B細胞|B細胞]]<ref name="PDR">{{cite journal | vauthors = Watkins RR, Lemonovich TL, Salata RA | title = An update on the association of vitamin D deficiency with common infectious diseases | journal = Canadian Journal of Physiology and Pharmacology | volume = 93 | issue = 5 | pages = 363–8 | date = May 2015 | pmid = 25741906 | doi = 10.1139/cjpp-2014-0352 }}</ref>。在體外，維他命D增加[[腎上腺|腎上腺]]{{le|髓質|Adrenal medulla}}細胞中[[酪氨酸羥化酶|酪氨酸羥化酶]]基因的表達，並影響了{{le|神經營養因子|Neurotrophic factors}}、[[一氧化氮合酶|一氧化氮合酶]]及[[谷胱甘肽|穀胱甘肽]]的合成<ref name="pmid9011759">{{cite journal | vauthors = Puchacz E, Stumpf WE, Stachowiak EK, Stachowiak MK | title = Vitamin D increases expression of the tyrosine hydroxylase gene in adrenal medullary cells | journal = Brain Research. Molecular Brain Research | volume = 36 | issue = 1 | pages = 193–6 | date = February 1996 | pmid = 9011759 | doi = 10.1016/0169-328X(95)00314-I }}</ref>。

維他命D受體的表達會隨年齡增長而降低，研究結果表明維他命D與肌肉力量、質量和功能直接相關，而所有這些都是影響運動員表現的重要因素<ref name=Angeline2013>{{cite journal | vauthors = Angeline ME, Gee AO, Shindle M, Warren RF, Rodeo SA | s2cid = 21395800 | title = The effects of vitamin D deficiency in athletes | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-sports-medicine_2013-02_41_2/page/461 | journal = The American Journal of Sports Medicine | volume = 41 | issue = 2 | pages = 461–4 | date = February 2013 | pmid = 23371942 | doi = 10.1177/0363546513475787 }}</ref>。

