==== 食品強化 ====
含有維他命D的加工食品強化包括了一些果汁和果汁飲品，[[代餐|代餐]]能量棒、[[大豆蛋白|大豆蛋白]]的飲料、某些奶酪和奶酪產品、麵粉製品、嬰兒[[配方奶粉|配方奶粉]]、許多早餐[[穀物片|穀物]]和[[乳|乳製品]]<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = de Lourdes Samaniego-Vaesken M, Alonso-Aperte E, Varela-Moreiras G | title = Vitamin food fortification today | journal = Food & Nutrition Research | volume = 56 | pages = 5459 | year = 2012 | pmid = 22481896 | pmc = 3319130 | doi = 10.3402/fnr.v56i0.5459 }}</ref><ref name="spiro">{{cite journal | vauthors = Spiro A, Buttriss JL | title = Vitamin D: An overview of vitamin D status and intake in Europe | journal = Nutrition Bulletin | volume = 39 | issue = 4 | pages = 322–350 | date = December 2014 | pmid = 25635171 | pmc = 4288313 | doi = 10.1111/nbu.12108 }}</ref>。

2016年，[[美国食品药品监督管理局|美國食品藥品監督管理局]]（FDA）修改了牛奶強化食品添加劑的法規<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fda.gov/food/food-additives-petitions/vitamin-d-milk-and-milk-alternatives |title=Vitamin D for Milk and Milk Alternatives |date=2016-07-15 |publisher=[[Food_and_Drug_Administration|Food and Drug Administration]] (FDA) |access-date=2017-02-22 |archive-date=2020-12-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201222015435/https://www.fda.gov/food/food-additives-petitions/vitamin-d-milk-and-milk-alternatives |dead-url=no }}{{PD-notice}}</ref>，規定每100克乳製品中的維他命D<sub>3</sub>含量不得超過42 IU（美國每[[夸脫|夸脫]]的400 IU）；每100克的[[植物奶|植物奶]]有84 IU的維他命D<sub>2</sub>（每夸脫800 IU）；而基於植物的[[酸奶|乳酪]]或在大豆飲料產品中，每100克含有89 IU（每夸脫800 IU）<ref name="fda16">{{cite web |url=https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2016/07/18/2016-16738/food-additives-permitted-for-direct-addition-to-food-for-human-consumption-vitamin-d2 |title=Federal Register: Food Additives Permitted for Direct Addition to Food for Human Consumption; Vitamin D2 |publisher=Food and Drug Administration, US Department of Health and Human Services |date=2016-07-18 |access-date=2017-02-22 |archive-date=2020-12-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201222015508/https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2016/07/18/2016-16738/food-additives-permitted-for-direct-addition-to-food-for-human-consumption-vitamin-d2 |dead-url=no }}{{PD-notice}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=6a3d5fc7d54cdaa0e9fd783b6063449d&mc=true&node=se21.3.172_1379&rgn=div8 |title=§172.379 Vitamin D2 |access-date=2019-07-16 |publisher=Electronic Code of Federal Regulations |archive-date=2020-12-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201222015511/https://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=6a3d5fc7d54cdaa0e9fd783b6063449d&mc=true&node=se21.3.172_1379&rgn=div8 |dead-url=no }}{{PD-notice}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=6a3d5fc7d54cdaa0e9fd783b6063449d&mc=true&node=se21.3.172_1380&rgn=div8 |title=§172.380 Vitamin D3 |access-date=2019-07-16 |publisher=Electronic Code of Federal Regulations |archive-date=2020-12-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201222015519/https://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=6a3d5fc7d54cdaa0e9fd783b6063449d&mc=true&node=se21.3.172_1380&rgn=div8 |dead-url=no }}{{PD-notice}}</ref>。植物奶被定義為由大豆、杏仁、米以及其他可替代為乳汁的植物來源而製成的飲料<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nutritionrefined.com/milk-alternatives/|title=Dairy Milk alternatives|last=|first=|date=2019-08-09|website=nutritionrefined|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201222015457/https://nutritionrefined.com/milk-alternatives/|archive-date=2020-12-22|access-date=|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://osoblanco.org/non-dairy-milk-best-alternatives-of-cow-milk/|title=Alternative to dairy milk|last=|first=|date=2020-01-16|website=osoblanco|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201222015535/https://osoblanco.org/non-dairy-milk-best-alternatives-of-cow-milk/|archive-date=2020-12-22|access-date=|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

雖然一些研究發現維他命D<sub>3</sub>可以更快地提高血液中25(OH)D的水平，並在體內保持更長的活躍時間<ref>{{Cite journal |title=Vitamin D<sub>2</sub> vs. vitamin D<sub>3</sub>: Are they one and the same? |year=2013 |journal=Nutrition Bulletin |volume=38 |issue=2 |pages=243–248 |author=Tripkovic L |doi=10.1111/nbu.12029}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Alshahrani F, Aljohani N | title = Vitamin D: deficiency, sufficiency and toxicity | journal = Nutrients | volume = 5 | issue = 9 | pages = 3605–16 | date = September 2013 | pmid = 24067388 | pmc = 3798924 | doi = 10.3390/nu5093605 }}</ref>，然而其他研究則認為維他命D<sub>2</sub>的來源具有相同的生物利用度，以及如維他命D<sub>3</sub>般有效用於提高和維持25（OH）D<ref name="keegan"/><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Biancuzzo RM, Clarke N, Reitz RE, Travison TG, Holick MF | title = Serum concentrations of 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D2 and 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D3 in response to vitamin D2 and vitamin D3 supplementation | journal = The Journal of Clinical Endocrinology and Metabolism | volume = 98 | issue = 3 | pages = 973–9 | date = March 2013 | pmid = 23386645 | pmc = 3590486 | doi = 10.1210/jc.2012-2114 }}</ref><ref name="borel">{{cite journal | vauthors = Borel P, Caillaud D, Cano NJ | s2cid = 9818323 | title = Vitamin D bioavailability: state of the art | journal = Critical Reviews in Food Science and Nutrition | volume = 55 | issue = 9 | pages = 1193–205 | year = 2015 | pmid = 24915331 | doi = 10.1080/10408398.2012.688897 }}</ref>。

=== 食物準備 ===
典型的食物中的維他命D含量會因烹飪而減少。煮沸、油炸和烘烤食品可保留原始維他命D的69{{en dash}}89％<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Jakobsen J, Knuthsen P | title = Stability of vitamin D in foodstuffs during cooking | journal = Food Chemistry | volume = 148 | pages = 170–5 | date = April 2014 | pmid = 24262542 | doi = 10.1016/j.foodchem.2013.10.043 }}</ref>。

== 維他命D缺乏症 ==
{{Main|维生素D缺乏症}}
[[File:Calcium_regulation.png|thumb]] 
全世界估計有十億人處於維他命D不足或缺乏<ref name=Angeline2013/>。維他命D不足的飲食加上日照不足會導致缺乏維他命D。兒童嚴重缺乏維他命D會導致患上[[佝僂病|佝僂病]]，這是一種骨骼的軟化和弱化的疾病，是一種發達國家中罕見的疾病<ref>{{cite web |date=2012-03-08 |title=Rickets |publisher=[[National_Health_Service|National Health Service]] |url=http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/Rickets/Pages/Introduction.aspx |access-date=2012-07-09 |archive-date=2017-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171011165432/http://www.nhs.uk/Conditions/Rickets/Pages/Introduction.aspx |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[維生素D缺乏症|維生素D缺乏症]]發現於世界各地的老年人中，在兒童及成年人中仍然很常見<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Munns CF, Shaw N, Kiely M, Specker BL, Thacher TD, Ozono K, Michigami T, Tiosano D, Mughal MZ, Mäkitie O, Ramos-Abad L, Ward L, DiMeglio LA, Atapattu N, Cassinelli H, Braegger C, Pettifor JM, Seth A, Idris HW, Bhatia V, Fu J, Goldberg G, Sävendahl L, Khadgawat R, Pludowski P, Maddock J, Hyppönen E, Oduwole A, Frew E, Aguiar M, Tulchinsky T, Butler G, Högler W | display-authors = 6 | title = Global Consensus Recommendations on Prevention and Management of Nutritional Rickets | journal = The Journal of Clinical Endocrinology and Metabolism | volume = 101 | issue = 2 | pages = 394–415 | date = February 2016 | pmid = 26745253 | pmc = 4880117 | doi = 10.1210/jc.2015-2175 }}</ref><ref name="pmid12014847">{{cite journal | vauthors = Eriksen EF, Glerup H | s2cid = 22112344 | title = Vitamin D deficiency and aging: implications for general health and osteoporosis | journal = Biogerontology | volume = 3 | issue = 1–2 | pages = 73–7 | year = 2002 | pmid = 12014847 | doi = 10.1023/A:1015263514765 }}</ref><ref name="Holick_2007">{{cite journal | vauthors = Holick MF | title = Vitamin D deficiency | journal = The New England Journal of Medicine | volume = 357 | issue = 3 | pages = 266–81 | date = July 2007 | pmid = 17634462 | doi = 10.1056/NEJMra070553 }}</ref>。缺乏症會導致骨骼礦化受損和骨骼損傷，從而導致出現骨骼軟化疾病<ref name="Brown_2008">{{cite book |first1=Judith E. |last1=Brown |first2=Janet |last2=Isaacs |first3=Bea |last3=Krinke |first4=Ellen |last4=Lechtenberg |first5=Maureen |last5=Murtaugh | name-list-format = vanc |title=Nutrition Through the Life Cycle |url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=TeQZBQAAQBAJ}}|date=2013-06-28|publisher=Cengage Learning|isbn=978-1-285-82025-5}}</ref>，包括兒童的佝僂病和成人的[[軟骨病|軟骨病]]。避免日曬會導致血液中的{{le|骨化二醇|Calcifediol}}（25-羥基維他命D）含量低<ref name="pmid18234141">{{cite journal | vauthors = Schoenmakers I, Goldberg GR, Prentice A | title = Abundant sunshine and vitamin D deficiency | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_british-journal-of-nutrition_2008-06_99_6/page/1171 | journal = The British Journal of Nutrition | volume = 99 | issue = 6 | pages = 1171–3 | date = June 2008 | pmid = 18234141 | pmc = 2758994 | doi = 10.1017/S0007114508898662 }}</ref>。維他命D缺乏會導致飲食中腸道對鈣的吸收下降至15％<ref name="Holick 2004" />。當不缺乏時，一個人通常吸收60-80％<ref name="Holick 2004" />。

=== 皮膚色素沉著 ===
生活在溫帶氣候中的深色皮膚的人被指出具低維他命D水平，但這個含義並不明確<ref name="pmid28620422">{{cite journal | vauthors = Lowe NM, Bhojani I | title = Special considerations for vitamin D in the south Asian population in the UK | journal = Therapeutic Advances in Musculoskeletal Disease | volume = 9 | issue = 6 | pages = 137–144 | date = June 2017 | pmid = 28620422 | pmc = 5466148 | doi = 10.1177/1759720X17704430 }}</ref><ref name="pmid24267433">{{cite journal | vauthors = O'Connor MY, Thoreson CK, Ramsey NL, Ricks M, Sumner AE | title = The uncertain significance of low vitamin D levels in African descent populations: a review of the bone and cardiometabolic literature | journal = Progress in Cardiovascular Diseases | volume = 56 | issue = 3 | pages = 261–9 | year = 2013 | pmid = 24267433 | pmc = 3894250 | doi = 10.1016/j.pcad.2013.10.015 }}</ref><ref name="pmid22688752">{{cite journal | vauthors = Freedman BI, Register TC | s2cid = 29026212 | title = Effect of race and genetics on vitamin D metabolism, bone and vascular health | journal = Nature Reviews. Nephrology | volume = 8 | issue = 8 | pages = 459–66 | date = June 2012 | pmid = 22688752 | doi = 10.1038/nrneph.2012.112 }}</ref>。深色皮膚的人產生維他命D的效率較低，因為其皮膚裡的黑色素會阻礙維他命D的合成<ref name="pmid28467404">{{cite journal | vauthors = Khalid AT, Moore CG, Hall C, Olabopo F, Rozario NL, Holick MF, Greenspan SL, Rajakumar K | display-authors = 6 | title = Utility of sun-reactive skin typing and melanin index for discerning vitamin D deficiency | journal = Pediatric Research | volume = 82 | issue = 3 | pages = 444–451 | date = September 2017 | pmid = 28467404 | pmc = 5570640 | doi = 10.1038/pr.2017.114 }}</ref>。維生素D缺乏症常見於美國的西班牙裔和非裔美國人，其維他命D水平會於冬季中顯著下降<ref name=holick2011/>。這是由於他們皮膚裡的黑色素所導致，黑色素是天然的防曬霜<ref  name=holick2011/>。

=== 骨骼健康 ===
==== 佝僂病 ====
{{Main|佝僂病}}
一種兒童時期的疾病 — 佝僂病，好發於3—18個月大之間<ref name=Wagner2008>{{cite journal | vauthors = Wagner CL, Greer FR | title = Prevention of rickets and vitamin D deficiency in infants, children, and adolescents | journal = Pediatrics | volume = 122 | issue = 5 | pages = 1142–52 | date = November 2008 | pmid = 18977996 | doi = 10.1542/peds.2008-1862 | doi-access = free }}</ref>，其特點是其骨骼生長受到阻礙，變得柔軟和虛弱，隨著幼童開始學步時，變形的[[長骨|長骨]]會因其體重的作用下而變得彎曲。北美和其他西方國家相繼有病例指出，首見於母乳餵養的初生嬰兒，以及膚色較深的人<ref name=Wagner2008/>。佝僂症的特徵是弓腿<ref name="Brown_2008"/>——可能是因缺乏鈣或磷及缺乏維他命D引起的；如今，該病主要在非洲，亞洲或中東等低收入國家中發現<ref name="pmid17943890">{{cite journal | vauthors = Lerch C, Meissner T | title = Interventions for the prevention of nutritional rickets in term born children | journal = The Cochrane Database of Systematic Reviews | issue = 4 | pages = CD006164 | date = October 2007 | pmid = 17943890 | doi = 10.1002/14651858.CD006164.pub2 | editor1-last = Lerch | editor1-first = Christian }}</ref>許多患有遺傳疾病的人（如偽維他命D缺乏性佝僂病）<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Zargar AH, Mithal A, Wani AI, Laway BA, Masoodi SR, Bashir MI, Ganie MA | title = Pseudovitamin D deficiency rickets--a report from the Indian subcontinent | journal = Postgraduate Medical Journal | volume = 76 | issue = 896 | pages = 369–72 | date = June 2000 | pmid = 10824056 | pmc = 1741602 | doi = 10.1136/pmj.76.896.369 }}</ref>。

孕婦[[維生素D缺乏症|維他命D缺乏症]]可能會導致嬰兒於出生前就出現明顯的骨骼疾病以及出生後骨骼質量受損<ref name=Elidrissy2016>{{cite journal | vauthors = Elidrissy AT | s2cid = 14727399 | title = The Return of Congenital Rickets, Are We Missing Occult Cases? | journal = Calcified Tissue International | volume = 99 | issue = 3 | pages = 227–36 | date = September 2016 | pmid = 27245342 | doi = 10.1007/s00223-016-0146-2 | type = Review }}</ref><ref name=PatersonAyoub2016>{{cite journal | vauthors = Paterson CR, Ayoub D | title = Congenital rickets due to vitamin D deficiency in the mothers | journal = Clinical Nutrition | volume = 34 | issue = 5 | pages = 793–8 | date = October 2015 | pmid = 25552383 | doi = 10.1016/j.clnu.2014.12.006 | type = Review }}</ref>。營養性佝僂病（Nutritional rickets）存在於一年四季都有陽光的國家，例如尼日利亞，並且可在不缺乏維他命D症的情況下發生<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Oramasionwu GE, Thacher TD, Pam SD, Pettifor JM, Abrams SA | title = Adaptation of calcium absorption during treatment of nutritional rickets in Nigerian children | journal = The British Journal of Nutrition | volume = 100 | issue = 2 | pages = 387–92 | date = August 2008 | pmid = 18197991 | doi = 10.1017/S0007114507901233 | url = https://espace.library.uq.edu.au/view/UQ:c3b1fb5/UQc3b1fb5_OA.pdf }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Fischer PR, Rahman A, Cimma JP, Kyaw-Myint TO, Kabir AR, Talukder K, Hassan N, Manaster BJ, Staab DB, Duxbury JM, Welch RM, Meisner CA, Haque S, Combs GF | display-authors = 6 | title = Nutritional rickets without vitamin D deficiency in Bangladesh | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-tropical-pediatrics_1999-10_45_5/page/291 | journal = Journal of Tropical Pediatrics | volume = 45 | issue = 5 | pages = 291–3 | date = October 1999 | pmid = 10584471 | doi = 10.1093/tropej/45.5.291 | doi-access = free }}</ref>。

儘管現在[[英國|英國]]很少發生佝僂病和骨質疏鬆症，但卻大量發生在某些移民社區，其中骨質疏鬆症的患者包括了穿著西式服裝、在看似在充足的日光下進行戶外活動的婦女<ref name="Dunnigan_1997">{{cite journal | vauthors = Dunnigan MG, Henderson JB | title = An epidemiological model of privational rickets and osteomalacia | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_proceedings-of-the-nutrition-society_1997-11_56_3/page/939 | journal = The Proceedings of the Nutrition Society | volume = 56 | issue = 3 | pages = 939–56 | date = November 1997 | pmid = 9483661 | doi = 10.1079/PNS19970100 | doi-access = free }}</ref>。除非飲食偏離以高攝入量的肉類、魚類和蛋以及低攝入量的高提取物[[穀物|穀物]]為特徵的西方雜食動物習慣，膚色較黝黑和減少陽光照射不會產生此病<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Robertson I, Ford JA, McIntosh WB, Dunnigan MG | title = The role of cereals in the aetiology of nutritional rickets: the lesson of the Irish National Nutrition Survey 1943-8 | journal = The British Journal of Nutrition | volume = 45 | issue = 1 | pages = 17–22 | date = January 1981 | pmid = 6970590 | doi = 10.1079/BJN19810073 | doi-access = free }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Clements MR |title=The problem of rickets in UK Asians |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-human-nutrition-and-dietetics_1989-04_2_2/page/105 |journal=Journal of Human Nutrition and Dietetics |volume=2 |issue=2 |year=1989 |doi=10.1111/j.1365-277X.1989.tb00015.x |pages=105–116}}</ref><ref name="Pettifor_2004">{{cite journal | vauthors = Pettifor JM | title = Nutritional rickets: deficiency of vitamin D, calcium, or both? | journal = The American Journal of Clinical Nutrition | volume = 80 | issue = 6 Suppl | pages = 1725S–9S | date = December 2004 | pmid = 15585795 | doi = 10.1093/ajcn/80.6.1725S | doi-access = free }}</ref>。佝僂病的飲食風險因素包括禁止食用動物食品<ref name="Dunnigan_1997"/><ref name="Dunnigan_2005">{{cite journal | vauthors = Dunnigan MG, Henderson JB, Hole DJ, Barbara Mawer E, Berry JL | title = Meat consumption reduces the risk of nutritional rickets and osteomalacia | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_british-journal-of-nutrition_2005-12_94_6/page/983 | journal = The British Journal of Nutrition | volume = 94 | issue = 6 | pages = 983–91 | date = December 2005 | pmid = 16351777 | doi = 10.1079/BJN20051558 | doi-access = free }}</ref>。

在大多數國家中，維他命D缺乏症仍然是嬰兒的主要病因，因為母乳中的維他命D含量不足，且社會風氣和氣候條件使人們避免獲得足購的日曬。在陽光充足的國家，例如尼日利亞，南非和孟加拉國，發病於較年長學步的幼會和兒童中，它被歸因於飲食中鈣攝入量低，這是只能有限地使用乳製品並佐以穀物為基礎的飲食<ref name="Pettifor_2004"/>。

佝僂病曾是美國的主要公衛問題。在[[丹佛|丹佛]]，同一緯度的紫外線強度比海平面強20％<ref>{{cite web |url=https://science.education.nih.gov/supplements/webversions/CellBiology/activities/activity5_database4.html |title=Cell Biology and Cancer Curriculum Supplement |publisher=Office of Science Education |access-date=2010-08-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100608033634/https://science.education.nih.gov/supplements/nih1/Cancer/activities/activity5_database4.htm |archive-date=2010-06-08 |dead-url=no }}{{PD-notice}}</ref>，在1920年代後期，近500名兒童中有近三分之二患有輕度的佝僂病<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Weick MT | title = A history of rickets in the United States | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-clinical-nutrition_1967-11_20_11/page/1234 | journal = The American Journal of Clinical Nutrition | volume = 20 | issue = 11 | pages = 1234–41 | date = November 1967 | pmid = 4862158 | doi = 10.1093/ajcn/20.11.1234 }}</ref>。20世紀美國飲食中的動物性蛋白比例增加<ref name="Dunnigan_2005"/><ref>{{cite book |vauthors=Garrison RH, Somer E |title=The Nutrition Desk Reference |url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=Z4hFKXI7EhsC}} |year=1997 |publisher=McGraw-Hill |isbn=978-0-87983-826-3}}</ref>加上牛奶的消耗量增加<ref name="Dupuis2002">{{cite book |first=E. Melanie |last=Dupuis |title=Nature's Perfect Food: How Milk Became America's Drink |url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=Nr1_u2DvDckC}}|date=2002-02-01|publisher=NYU Press|isbn=978-0-8147-1938-1 | name-list-format = vanc}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Teegarden D, Lyle RM, Proulx WR, Johnston CC, Weaver CM | title = Previous milk consumption is associated with greater bone density in young women | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-clinical-nutrition_1999-05_69_5/page/1014 | journal = The American Journal of Clinical Nutrition | volume = 69 | issue = 5 | pages = 1014–7 | date = May 1999 | pmid = 10232644 | doi = 10.1093/ajcn/69.5.1014 | doi-access = free }}</ref>，強化相對維他命D含量較少的情況下，佝僂病病例的數字急劇下降<ref name="Holick 2004" />。同樣，在美國和加拿大，維他命D強化牛奶、嬰兒補充劑和維他命補充劑已消除大多數佝僂病兒童所患有的脂肪吸收不良<ref name="Brown_2008"/>。

==== 骨質疏鬆症和骨軟化病 ====
{{Main|骨質疏鬆症|[[軟骨病|軟骨病]]}}
[[骨質疏鬆症|骨質疏鬆症]]是成年人的維他命D缺乏引起的疾病。該疾病的特徵是使骨骼軟化，導致脊柱彎曲、腿部彎曲、{{le|近端|Anatomical terms of location#Proximal and distal}}肌肉無力、骨骼脆弱，增加骨折風險<ref name="Insel_2006"/>。骨質疏鬆症減少了鈣質的吸收並增加了骨骼中鈣質的流失，那增加了骨折的風險。骨質疏鬆症通常出現於25-羥基維他命D水平低於約10ng/mL時<ref name="Holick_2006"/>。儘管人們認為軟骨病的影響可導致慢性[[肌肉骨骼系統|肌肉骨骼系統]][[疼痛|疼痛]]<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Holick MF | title = Vitamin D: A millenium perspective | journal = Journal of Cellular Biochemistry | volume = 88 | issue = 2 | pages = 296–307 | date = February 2003 | pmid = 12520530 | doi = 10.1002/jcb.10338 }}</ref>，這裡沒有具說服力的證據指出慢性疼痛患者出現較低的維他命D水平<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Straube S, Andrew Moore R, Derry S, McQuay HJ | s2cid = 17244398 | title = Vitamin D and chronic pain | journal = Pain | volume = 141 | issue = 1–2 | pages = 10–3 | date = January 2009 | pmid = 19084336 | doi = 10.1016/j.pain.2008.11.010 }}</ref>，或該補充劑可減輕慢性非特異性肌肉骨骼疼痛<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Gaikwad M, Vanlint S, Mittinity M, Moseley GL, Stocks N | s2cid = 30189971 | title = Does vitamin D supplementation alleviate chronic nonspecific musculoskeletal pain? A systematic review and meta-analysis | journal = Clinical Rheumatology | volume = 36 | issue = 5 | pages = 1201–1208 | date = May 2017 | pmid = 26861032 | doi = 10.1007/s10067-016-3205-1 | url = https://www.researchgate.net/publication/293637550 }}</ref>。

== 補充劑的使用 ==
維他命D補充劑是預防或治療[[佝僂病|佝僂病]]的一個可靠方法，然而它對非骨骼健康的影響尚未確定<ref name=Balk09>{{cite journal | vauthors = Chung M, Balk EM, Brendel M, Ip S, Lau J, Lee J, Lichtenstein A, Patel K, Raman G, Tatsioni A, Terasawa T, Trikalinos TA | display-authors = 6 | title = Vitamin D and calcium: a systematic review of health outcomes | journal = Evidence Report/Technology Assessment | issue = 183 | pages = 1–420 | date = August 2009 | pmid = 20629479 | pmc = 4781105 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Theodoratou E, Tzoulaki I, Zgaga L, Ioannidis JP | title = Vitamin D and multiple health outcomes: umbrella review of systematic reviews and meta-analyses of observational studies and randomised trials | journal = BMJ | volume = 348 | pages = g2035 | date = April 2014 | pmid = 24690624 | pmc = 3972415 | doi = 10.1136/bmj.g2035 }}</ref>。2013年的一項評論發現，除了可以降低老年人的死亡率外，並沒有發現補充劑對非骨骼疾病發生率有任何影響<ref name=Aut2013>{{cite journal | vauthors = Autier P, Boniol M, Pizot C, Mullie P | title = Vitamin D status and ill health: a systematic review | journal = The Lancet. Diabetes & Endocrinology | volume = 2 | issue = 1 | pages = 76–89 | date = January 2014 | pmid = 24622671 | doi = 10.1016/S2213-8587(13)70165-7 }}</ref>。維他命D補充劑不會改變[[心肌梗塞|心肌梗塞]]、[[中風|中風]]或[[腦血管疾病|腦血管疾病]]、癌症、膝蓋[[骨關節炎|骨關節炎]]的結果<ref name=Futil2014 /><ref name="Hussain_2017">{{cite journal | vauthors = Hussain S, Singh A, Akhtar M, Najmi AK | s2cid = 23994681 | title = Vitamin D supplementation for the management of knee osteoarthritis: a systematic review of randomized controlled trials | journal = Rheumatology International | volume = 37 | issue = 9 | pages = 1489–1498 | date = September 2017 | pmid = 28421358 | doi = 10.1007/s00296-017-3719-0 }}</ref>。維他命D水平可能是疾病引起，而非引致疾病的發生<ref name=Aut2013/>。美國{{le|醫學研究院|National Academy of Medicine}}（IOM）的一份報告指出：「跟[[癌症|癌症]]、[[心血管疾病|心血管疾病]]及[[高血壓|高血壓]]，以及[[糖尿病|糖尿病]]與代謝綜合症相關的結果，跌倒和身體機能、免疫功能和[[自體免疫性疾病|自體免疫性疾病]]、感染、神經心理機能及[[妊娠毒血症|子癇前症]]都不能與鈣質或維他命D攝入可靠地聯繫在一起，並且經常出現相互矛盾<ref name="Ross_2011"/>。」一些研究人員聲稱，IOM的建議過於明確，在計算與骨骼健康相關的維他命D水平時犯了數學上的錯誤<ref name=Maxmen2011/>。IOM小組成員堅持認為他們使用了「飲食建議的標準程序」，並且該報告是完全基於這些數據。維他命D補充劑的研究，包括了大規模的臨床試驗，繼續正在進行中<ref name=Maxmen2011>{{cite journal | vauthors = Maxmen A | title = Nutrition advice: the vitamin D-lemma | journal = Nature | volume = 475 | issue = 7354 | pages = 23–5 | date = July 2011 | pmid = 21734684 | doi = 10.1038/475023a | url = http://www.nature.com/news/2011/110706/pdf/475023a.pdf | doi-access = free | access-date = 2012-01-02 | archive-date = 2020-08-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200803081923/https://www.nature.com/news/2011/110706/pdf/475023a.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

=== 骨骼健康 ===
在一般情況下，人們普遍認為維他命D補充劑有助預防骨質疏鬆症的觀點並沒有很好的證據支持<ref name=Futil2014/>。它通常用於預防這種疾病，因此那些沒有維他命D缺乏症的人可能沒有需要<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Reid IR, Bolland MJ, Grey A | title = Effects of vitamin D supplements on bone mineral density: a systematic review and meta-analysis | journal = Lancet | volume = 383 | issue = 9912 | pages = 146–55 | date = January 2014 | pmid = 24119980 | doi = 10.1016/s0140-6736(13)61647-5 }}</ref>。對於患有骨質疏鬆症的老年人，把維他命D跟鈣質一同服用可能有助於預防髖部骨折，但它也會輕微增加了患上胃部及腎臟疾病的風險<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Avenell A, Mak JC, O'Connell D | title = Vitamin D and vitamin D analogues for preventing fractures in post-menopausal women and older men | journal = The Cochrane Database of Systematic Reviews | volume = 4 | issue = 4 | pages = CD000227 | date = April 2014 | pmid = 24729336 | pmc = 7032685 | doi = 10.1002/14651858.CD000227.pub4 }}</ref>。在65歲以上的人裡，調高劑量的維他命D補充劑可以降低骨折風險<ref name="pmid22762317">{{cite journal | vauthors = Bischoff-Ferrari HA, Willett WC, Orav EJ, Oray EJ, Lips P, Meunier PJ, Lyons RA, Flicker L, Wark J, Jackson RD, Cauley JA, Meyer HE, Pfeifer M, Sanders KM, Stähelin HB, Theiler R, Dawson-Hughes B | s2cid = 24338997 | display-authors = 6 | title = A pooled analysis of vitamin D dose requirements for fracture prevention | journal = The New England Journal of Medicine | volume = 367 | issue = 1 | pages = 40–9 | date = July 2012 | pmid = 22762317 | doi = 10.1056/NEJMoa1109617 | url = https://research.vu.nl/ws/files/709966/300335.pdf | hdl = 1871/48765 | access-date = 2020-08-16 | archive-date = 2020-12-15 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201215140446/https://research.vu.nl/ws/files/709966/300335.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>。對於獨立生活的人而言，其影響是很小甚至是沒有的<ref name="ReferenceA">{{cite journal | vauthors = Chung M, Lee J, Terasawa T, Lau J, Trikalinos TA | title = Vitamin D with or without calcium supplementation for prevention of cancer and fractures: an updated meta-analysis for the U.S. Preventive Services Task Force | journal = Annals of Internal Medicine | volume = 155 | issue = 12 | pages = 827–38 | date = December 2011 | pmid = 22184690 | doi = 10.7326/0003-4819-155-12-201112200-00005 | doi-access = free }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Zhao JG, Zeng XT, Wang J, Liu L | title = Association Between Calcium or Vitamin D Supplementation and Fracture Incidence in Community-Dwelling Older Adults: A Systematic Review and Meta-analysis | journal = JAMA | volume = 318 | issue = 24 | pages = 2466–2482 | date = December 2017 | pmid = 29279934 | pmc = 5820727 | doi = 10.1001/jama.2017.19344 }}</ref>。低血清維他命D水平跟[[跌倒|跌倒]]與低{{le|骨質密度|Bone density}}有關<ref name=Bone07>{{cite journal | vauthors = Cranney A, Horsley T, O'Donnell S, Weiler H, Puil L, Ooi D, Atkinson S, Ward L, Moher D, Hanley D, Fang M, Yazdi F, Garritty C, Sampson M, Barrowman N, Tsertsvadze A, Mamaladze V | display-authors = 6 | title = Effectiveness and safety of vitamin D in relation to bone health | journal = Evidence Report/Technology Assessment | issue = 158 | pages = 1–235 | date = August 2007 | pmid = 18088161 | pmc = 4781354 }}</ref>。然而，服用額外的維他命D似乎並沒有改變風險<ref name="pmid24768505">{{cite journal | vauthors = Bolland MJ, Grey A, Gamble GD, Reid IR | title = Vitamin D supplementation and falls: a trial sequential meta-analysis | journal = The Lancet. Diabetes & Endocrinology | volume = 2 | issue = 7 | pages = 573–80 | date = July 2014 | pmid = 24768505 | doi = 10.1016/S2213-8587(14)70068-3 }}</ref>。維他命D缺乏症的運動員，特別是那些從事接觸運動的人，他們會增加患上[[疲勞性骨折|疲勞性骨折]]及/或嚴重骨折的風險。補充劑最大的好處可見於25（OH）D血清水平不足（<30{{nbsp}}ng/mL），或25（OH）D血清水平嚴重不足（<25{{nbsp}}ng/mL）的人身上。血清25（OH）D濃度升高穩定在50 ng/mL時，可觀察到風險增加，而在超過這一點的水平上，沒有其他可見的額外好處<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Shuler FD, Wingate MK, Moore GH, Giangarra C | title = Sports health benefits of vitamin d | journal = Sports Health | volume = 4 | issue = 6 | pages = 496–501 | date = November 2012 | pmid = 24179588 | pmc = 3497950 | doi = 10.1177/1941738112461621 }}</ref>。

由於發現了越來越多的有益於骨骼健康的證據，儘管它沒有找到其他益處的充分證據，[[美國食品藥品監督管理局|美國食品藥品監督管理局]]（FDA）自2016年5月起要求製造商於[[營養標籤|營養標籤]]上聲明維他命D的含量，以作為「具有公共衛生意義的營養素」。每年食品銷售額少於$1,000萬美元的小型製造商透過提議的截止日期延長，將必須在2021年1月1日之前遵守法規，而較大的則必須在2020年1月1日之前遵守<ref name="FDAdelay" />。單一成分糖（例如蜜糖和楓糖漿）及某些蔓越莓產品的製造商必須在2021年7月1日之前作出更改<ref name="FDAdelay" />。

=== 癌症 ===
維他命D補充劑因其聲稱的抗癌特性而被廣泛銷售<ref name=abc>{{cite journal | vauthors = Byers T | title = Anticancer vitamins du Jour--The ABCED's so far | journal = American Journal of Epidemiology | volume = 172 | issue = 1 | pages = 1–3 | date = July 2010 | pmid = 20562190 | pmc = 2892535 | doi = 10.1093/aje/kwq112 | type = Review }}</ref>。在觀察性研究中，維他命D水平低與某些癌症的發生風險之間存在著關聯<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Feldman D, Krishnan AV, Swami S, Giovannucci E, Feldman BJ | s2cid = 24164628 | title = The role of vitamin D in reducing cancer risk and progression | journal = Nature Reviews. Cancer | volume = 14 | issue = 5 | pages = 342–57 | date = May 2014 | pmid = 24705652 | doi = 10.1038/nrc3691 }}</ref>。然而，尚未清楚在飲食中或作為維他命D補充劑是否會影響[[癌症|癌症]]的風險。評論把證據描述為「因果關係不一致，不確定，並且不足以告知營養需求」<ref name="Ross_2011"/>，和「不足以得出結論」<ref name="ReferenceA"/>。2014年的一篇評論發現補充劑對癌症風險沒有顯著影響<ref name=Futil2014/>。

2014年的另一篇評論得出結論，維他命D<sub>3</sub>可以降低癌症的死亡風險（在5年內接受治療的150人中，死亡人數減少了1人），但注意到對數據質量的擔憂<ref name=Bj2014 />。儘管有證據表明維他命D缺乏症對某些癌症結果更糟<ref name="Buttigliero">{{cite journal | vauthors = Buttigliero C, Monagheddu C, Petroni P, Saini A, Dogliotti L, Ciccone G, Berruti A | title = Prognostic role of vitamin d status and efficacy of vitamin D supplementation in cancer patients: a systematic review | journal = The Oncologist | volume = 16 | issue = 9 | pages = 1215–27 | year = 2011 | pmid = 21835895 | pmc = 3228169 | doi = 10.1634/theoncologist.2011-0098 }}</ref>，在診斷時有較高的25-羥基維他命D水平與更好的結果有關<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Li M, Chen P, Li J, Chu R, Xie D, Wang H | title = Review: the impacts of circulating 25-hydroxyvitamin D levels on cancer patient outcomes: a systematic review and meta-analysis | journal = The Journal of Clinical Endocrinology and Metabolism | volume = 99 | issue = 7 | pages = 2327–36 | date = July 2014 | pmid = 24780061 | doi = 10.1210/jc.2013-4320 | doi-access = free }}</ref>。

=== 心血管疾病 ===
服用維他命D補充劑並不能有效降低[[中風|中風]]、[[腦血管疾病|腦血管疾病]]、[[心肌梗塞|心肌梗塞]]或[[冠狀動脈疾病|冠狀動脈疾病]]的風險<ref name=Futil2014>{{cite journal | vauthors = Bolland MJ, Grey A, Gamble GD, Reid IR | title = The effect of vitamin D supplementation on skeletal, vascular, or cancer outcomes: a trial sequential meta-analysis | journal = The Lancet. Diabetes & Endocrinology | volume = 2 | issue = 4 | pages = 307–20 | date = April 2014 | pmid = 24703049 | doi = 10.1016/S2213-8587(13)70212-2 | type = Meta-analysis }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Barbarawi M, Kheiri B, Zayed Y, Barbarawi O, Dhillon H, Swaid B, Yelangi A, Sundus S, Bachuwa G, Alkotob ML, Manson JE | display-authors = 6 | title = Vitamin D Supplementation and Cardiovascular Disease Risks in More Than 83 000 Individuals in 21 Randomized Clinical Trials: A Meta-analysis | journal = JAMA Cardiology | volume = 4 | issue = 8 | pages = 765–776 | date = August 2019 | pmid = 31215980 | pmc = 6584896 | doi = 10.1001/jamacardio.2019.1870 }}</ref>。補充劑可能對[[血壓|血壓]]並沒有影響<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Beveridge LA, Struthers AD, Khan F, Jorde R, Scragg R, Macdonald HM, Alvarez JA, Boxer RS, Dalbeni A, Gepner AD, Isbel NM, Larsen T, Nagpal J, Petchey WG, Stricker H, Strobel F, Tangpricha V, Toxqui L, Vaquero MP, Wamberg L, Zittermann A, Witham MD | display-authors = 6 | title = Effect of Vitamin D Supplementation on Blood Pressure: A Systematic Review and Meta-analysis Incorporating Individual Patient Data | journal = JAMA Internal Medicine | volume = 175 | issue = 5 | pages = 745–54 | date = May 2015 | pmid = 25775274 | pmc = 5966296 | doi = 10.1001/jamainternmed.2015.0237 }}</ref>。

=== 免疫系統 ===
==== 自身免疫性疾病 ====
儘管有初步數據表明哮喘跟維他命D水平低有關，但支持補充劑對哮喘患者具有益作用的證據則沒有證據支持<ref name="pmid22742645">{{cite journal | vauthors = Hart PH | title = Vitamin D supplementation, moderate sun exposure, and control of immune diseases | journal = Discovery Medicine | volume = 13 | issue = 73 | pages = 397–404 | date = June 2012 | pmid = 22742645 | doi =  | url = http://www.discoverymedicine.com/Prue-H-Hart/2012/06/14/vitamin-d-supplementation-moderate-sun-exposure-and-control-of-immune-diseases/ | access-date = 2020-08-17 | archive-date = 2020-08-12 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200812212626/https://www.discoverymedicine.com/Prue-H-Hart/2012/06/14/vitamin-d-supplementation-moderate-sun-exposure-and-control-of-immune-diseases/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。一項評論發現，維他命D補充劑可以減少用於抑制輕度至中度哮喘發作頻率類固醇的需要，並且這種補充對日常哮喘症狀沒有影響<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Martineau AR, Cates CJ, Urashima M, Jensen M, Griffiths AP, Nurmatov U, Sheikh A, Griffiths CJ | display-authors = 6 | title = Vitamin D for the management of asthma | journal = The Cochrane Database of Systematic Reviews | volume = 9 | pages = CD011511 | date = September 2016 | pmid = 27595415 | pmc = 6457769 | doi = 10.1002/14651858.cd011511.pub2 }}</ref>。在一般情況下，維他命D補充劑是並不建議用於治療或預防哮喘<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Paul G, Brehm JM, Alcorn JF, Holguín F, Aujla SJ, Celedón JC | title = Vitamin D and asthma | journal = American Journal of Respiratory and Critical Care Medicine | volume = 185 | issue = 2 | pages = 124–32 | date = January 2012 | pmid = 22016447 | pmc = 3297088 | doi = 10.1164/rccm.201108-1502CI }}</ref>。

==== 發炎性腸病 ====
維他命D含量低與兩種人類[[炎症性腸病|炎症性腸病]]（IBD）的主要形式有關：[[克隆氏症|克隆氏症]]及[[潰瘍性結腸炎|潰瘍性結腸炎]]<ref name="IBD2015">{{cite journal | vauthors = Del Pinto R, Pietropaoli D, Chandar AK, Ferri C, Cominelli F | title = Association Between Inflammatory Bowel Disease and Vitamin D Deficiency: A Systematic Review and Meta-analysis | journal = Inflammatory Bowel Diseases | volume = 21 | issue = 11 | pages = 2708–17 | date = November 2015 | pmid = 26348447 | pmc = 4615394 | doi = 10.1097/MIB.0000000000000546 }}</ref>。對於患有維他命D缺乏症的IBD患者進行維他命D治療的綜合分析顯示，補充劑可有效糾正維他命D水平，並與臨床疾病活動及生化標誌物指標的改進有關<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Guzman-Prado Y, Samson O, Segal JP, Limdi JK, Hayee B | title = Vitamin D Therapy in Adults With Inflammatory Bowel Disease: A Systematic Review and Meta-Analysis | journal = Inflammatory Bowel Diseases | date = May 2020 | pmid = 32385487 | doi = 10.1093/ibd/izaa087 }}</ref>。

==== 傳染病與COVID-19 ====
通常，維他命D的功能是激活[[先天免疫系統|先天免疫系統]]和抑制[[後天免疫系統|後天免疫系統]]<ref name="pmid21419266">{{Cite book |vauthors=Hewison M |chapter=Vitamin D and innate and adaptive immunity |volume=86 |pages=23–62 |year=2011 |pmid=21419266 |doi=10.1016/B978-0-12-386960-9.00002-2 |isbn=9780123869609 |series=Vitamins & Hormones|title=Vitamins and the Immune System }}</ref>。缺乏症跟[[病毒性疾病|病毒性疾病]]的風險或嚴重性增加有關，包括[[人類免疫缺陷病毒|HIV]]<ref name="Viral2011">{{cite journal | vauthors = Beard JA, Bearden A, Striker R | title = Vitamin D and the anti-viral state | journal = Journal of Clinical Virology | volume = 50 | issue = 3 | pages = 194–200 | date = March 2011 | pmid = 21242105 | pmc = 3308600 | doi = 10.1016/j.jcv.2010.12.006 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Spector SA | title = Vitamin D and HIV: letting the sun shine in | journal = Topics in Antiviral Medicine | volume = 19 | issue = 1 | pages = 6–10 | date = 2011 | pmid = 21852710 | pmc = 6148856 }}</ref>。維他命D的含量過低似乎是[[結核病|結核病]]的風險因素<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Nnoaham KE, Clarke A | title = Low serum vitamin D levels and tuberculosis: a systematic review and meta-analysis | journal = International Journal of Epidemiology | volume = 37 | issue = 1 | pages = 113–9 | date = February 2008 | pmid = 18245055 | doi = 10.1093/ije/dym247 | citeseerx = 10.1.1.513.3969 }}</ref>，在歷史上一直被用作治療用途<ref name=Tub2011>{{cite journal | vauthors = Luong K, Nguyen LT | title = Impact of vitamin D in the treatment of tuberculosis | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-the-medical-sciences_2011-06_341_6/page/493 | journal = The American Journal of the Medical Sciences | volume = 341 | issue = 6 | pages = 493–8 | date = June 2011 | pmid = 21289501 | doi = 10.1097/MAJ.0b013e3182070f47 | s2cid = 18802134 }}</ref>。補充劑可稍微降低急性[[呼吸道感染|呼吸道感染]]的風險和嚴重程度，也可減輕[[哮喘|哮喘]]的惡化<ref name="Bergman">{{cite journal | vauthors = Bergman P, Lindh AU, Björkhem-Bergman L, Lindh JD | title = Vitamin D and Respiratory Tract Infections: A Systematic Review and Meta-Analysis of Randomized Controlled Trials | journal = PLOS ONE | volume = 8 | issue = 6 | pages = e65835 | year = 2013 | pmid = 23840373 | pmc = 3686844 | doi = 10.1371/journal.pone.0065835 | bibcode = 2013PLoSO...865835B }}</ref><ref name="bmj2017">{{cite journal | vauthors = Martineau AR, Jolliffe DA, Hooper RL, Greenberg L, Aloia JF, Bergman P, Dubnov-Raz G, Esposito S, Ganmaa D, Ginde AA, Goodall EC, Grant CC, Griffiths CJ, Janssens W, Laaksi I, Manaseki-Holland S, Mauger D, Murdoch DR, Neale R, Rees JR, Simpson S, Stelmach I, Kumar GT, Urashima M, Camargo CA | display-authors = 6 | title = Vitamin D supplementation to prevent acute respiratory tract infections: systematic review and meta-analysis of individual participant data | journal = BMJ | volume = 356 | pages = i6583 | date = February 2017 | pmid = 28202713 | pmc = 5310969 | doi = 10.1136/bmj.i6583 | url = http://www.bmj.com/content/356/bmj.i6583 | access-date = 2020-08-17 | archive-date = 2021-02-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210202235636/https://www.bmj.com/content/356/bmj.i6583 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。這裡沒有證據表明維他命D影響5歲以下兒童的呼吸道感染<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Yakoob MY, Salam RA, Khan FR, Bhutta ZA | title = Vitamin D supplementation for preventing infections in children under five years of age | journal = The Cochrane Database of Systematic Reviews | volume = 11 | pages = CD008824 | date = November 2016 | pmid = 27826955 | pmc = 5450876 | doi = 10.1002/14651858.cd008824.pub2 }}</ref>。

[[2019冠状病毒病疫情|2019冠状病毒病疫情]]引起人們對維他命D缺乏症可能是呼吸道感染的危險因素的關注<ref name=bmj2017/><ref name="rhodes">{{cite journal | vauthors = Rhodes JM, Subramanian S, Laird E, Kenny RA | title = Editorial: low population mortality from COVID-19 in countries south of latitude 35 degrees North supports vitamin D as a factor determining severity | journal = Alimentary Pharmacology & Therapeutics | volume = 51 | issue = 12 | pages = 1434–1437 | date = June 2020 | pmid = 32311755 | pmc = 7264531 | doi = 10.1111/apt.15777 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Grant WB, Lahore H, McDonnell SL, Baggerly CA, French CB, Aliano JL, Bhattoa HP | title = Evidence that Vitamin D Supplementation Could Reduce Risk of Influenza and COVID-19 Infections and Deaths | journal = Nutrients | volume = 12 | issue = 4 | pages = 988 | date = April 2020 | pmid = 32252338 | pmc = 7231123 | doi = 10.3390/nu12040988 }}</ref><ref name="ebadi">{{cite journal | vauthors = Ebadi M, Montano-Loza AJ | title = Perspective: improving vitamin D status in the management of COVID-19 | journal = European Journal of Clinical Nutrition | volume = 74 | issue = 6 | pages = 856–859 | date = June 2020 | pmid = 32398871 | pmc = 7216123 | doi = 10.1038/s41430-020-0661-0 }}</ref>，但只有初步證據證明維他命D缺乏症和COVID-19感染之間存在直接關聯<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = D'Avolio A, Avataneo V, Manca A, Cusato J, De Nicolò A, Lucchini R, Keller F, Cantù M | display-authors = 6 | title = 25-Hydroxyvitamin D Concentrations Are Lower in Patients with Positive PCR for SARS-CoV-2 | journal = Nutrients | volume = 12 | issue = 5 | pages = 1359 | date = May 2020 | pmid = 32397511 | doi = 10.3390/nu12051359 | pmc = 7285131 }}</ref>。一項英國的研究發現，當對[[族群|族群]]等潛在的混雜因素進行調整時，先前所測量得到的維他命D水平跟COVID-19感染的發生率之間並沒有關聯<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Hastie CE, Mackay DF, Ho F, Celis-Morales CA, Katikireddi SV, Niedzwiedz CL, Jani BD, Welsh P, Mair FS, Gray SR, O'Donnell CA, Gill JM, Sattar N, Pell JP | display-authors = 6 | title = Vitamin D concentrations and COVID-19 infection in UK Biobank | journal = Diabetes & Metabolic Syndrome | volume = 14 | issue = 4 | pages = 561–565 | date = May 2020 | pmid = 32413819 | pmc = 7204679 | doi = 10.1016/j.dsx.2020.04.050 }}</ref>。維他命D缺乏症在許多COVID-19病例和死亡人數最多的國家中很普遍，例如美國，西班牙，英國，意大利和伊朗<ref name=rhodes/><ref name=ebadi/>。一份由UK NICE發表的證據摘要得出結論，這裡沒有任何證據支持以維他命D補充劑用作預防或治療COVID‑19<ref name="NICEJune2020">{{cite web |last1=NICE |title=Key messages {{!}}  COVID-19 rapid evidence summary: vitamin D for COVID-19 {{!}} Advice {{!}} NICE |url=https://www.nice.org.uk/advice/es28/chapter/Key-messages |website=www.nice.org.uk |accessdate=2020-06-29 |archive-date=2020-12-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201215140516/https://www.nice.org.uk/advice/es28/chapter/Key-messages |dead-url=no }}</ref>。根據ClinicalTrials.gov，一些{{le|第二至四期臨床試驗|Phases of clinical research}}正在進行以評估使用維他命D預防或治療COVID‑19感染的用途。截至2020年5月，大多數研究都處於初步階段，尚未完成<ref name=vitD-clintrials>{{cite web|url=https://clinicaltrials.gov/ct2/results?cond=COVID-19&term=vitamin+D&cntry=&state=&city=&dist=|title=International clinical trials assessing vitamin D in people with COVID-19|publisher=ClinicalTrials.gov, US National Library of Medicine|date=May 2020|access-date=2020-05-20|archive-date=2020-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201006214952/https://clinicaltrials.gov/ct2/results?cond=COVID-19&term=vitamin+D&cntry=&state=&city=&dist=%2F|dead-url=no}}</ref>。大多數試驗的設計都是用以研究維他命D缺乏症的COVID-19感染者<ref name=vitD-clintrials/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-020-77093-z|doi=10.1038/s41598-020-77093-z|title=nature research Scientific Reports 2020 10:20191 OPEN ACCESS Analysis of vitamin D level among asymptonmatic and critically ill COVID-19 patients and its correlation with inflammatory markers (CC BY 4.0 creative commons)|author=Anshul Jain, Rachna Chaurasia, Narendra Singh Sengar, Mayank Singh, Sachin Mahor & Sumit Narain|accessdate=2020-11-25|archive-date=2020-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207122635/https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-020-77093-z|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。

=== 其他狀況 ===
* '''糖尿病''' — 2014年的系統評價的結論是，現有的研究顯示，沒有證據表明維他命D<sub>3</sub>補充劑對葡萄糖穩態或[[糖尿病|糖尿病]]的預防有效<ref name="pmid25062463">{{cite journal | vauthors = Seida JC, Mitri J, Colmers IN, Majumdar SR, Davidson MB, Edwards AL, Hanley DA, Pittas AG, Tjosvold L, Johnson JA | display-authors = 6 | title = Clinical review: Effect of vitamin D3 supplementation on improving glucose homeostasis and preventing diabetes: a systematic review and meta-analysis | journal = The Journal of Clinical Endocrinology and Metabolism | volume = 99 | issue = 10 | pages = 3551–60 | date = October 2014 | pmid = 25062463 | pmc = 4483466 | doi = 10.1210/jc.2014-2136 | type = Review }}</ref>。2016年的一篇評論文章報告指，儘管越來越多的證據表明維他命D缺乏可能是糖尿病的風險因素，關於維他命D水平跟糖尿病的全面證據是互相矛盾的，這方面需要進一步研究<ref name="pmid26981182">{{cite journal | vauthors = Nakashima A, Yokoyama K, Yokoo T, Urashima M | title = Role of vitamin D in diabetes mellitus and chronic kidney disease | journal = World Journal of Diabetes | volume = 7 | issue = 5 | pages = 89–100 | date = March 2016 | pmid = 26981182 | pmc = 4781904 | doi = 10.4239/wjd.v7.i5.89 | type = Review }}</ref>。

* '''抑鬱症''' — 維他命D補充劑對於抑鬱症狀的臨床試驗普遍是低質量並沒有顯示整體效果，儘管小群分析顯示，對於具有臨床上明顯的抑鬱症狀或抑鬱障礙的參與者俱有中度療效<ref name="Shaffer">{{cite journal | vauthors = Shaffer JA, Edmondson D, Wasson LT, Falzon L, Homma K, Ezeokoli N, Li P, Davidson KW | display-authors = 6 | title = Vitamin D supplementation for depressive symptoms: a systematic review and meta-analysis of randomized controlled trials | journal = Psychosomatic Medicine | volume = 76 | issue = 3 | pages = 190–6 | date = April 2014 | pmid = 24632894 | pmc = 4008710 | doi = 10.1097/psy.0000000000000044 }}</ref>。

* '''認知與癡呆''' — 一份臨床研究的系統性評價維他命D水平低與[[認知障礙|認知障礙]]之間存在著關聯，以及患上[[阿茲海默症|阿茲海默症]]有更高的風險。然而，較低的維他命D濃度也跟營養不良和戶外活動時間減少有關。因此無法確定對於增加存在認知障礙的替代解釋，以及由此而來的維他命D水平與認知之間的直接因果關係<ref name="pmid23008220">{{cite journal | vauthors = Balion C, Griffith LE, Strifler L, Henderson M, Patterson C, Heckman G, Llewellyn DJ, Raina P | display-authors = 6 | title = Vitamin D, cognition, and dementia: a systematic review and meta-analysis | journal = Neurology | volume = 79 | issue = 13 | pages = 1397–405 | date = September 2012 | pmid = 23008220 | pmc = 3448747 | doi = 10.1212/WNL.0b013e31826c197f }}</ref>。

* '''體重減少''' — 儘管假設維他命D補充劑在除了{{le|卡路里限制|Calorie restriction}}以外對[[肥胖症|肥胖症]]來說可能是一種有效的治療方法，一項系統性評價發現補充劑與體重或[[脂肪組織|脂肪量]]沒有關聯<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Pathak K, Soares MJ, Calton EK, Zhao Y, Hallett J | title = Vitamin D supplementation and body weight status: a systematic review and meta-analysis of randomized controlled trials | journal = Obesity Reviews | volume = 15 | issue = 6 | pages = 528–37 | date = June 2014 | pmid = 24528624 | doi = 10.1111/obr.12162 }}</ref>。2016年的一份[[元分析|元分析]]發現減輕體重可改善循環維他命D的狀態，這表明脂肪量可能跟血液中維他命D的水平成反比<ref name="mallard">{{cite journal | vauthors = Mallard SR, Howe AS, Houghton LA | title = Vitamin D status and weight loss: a systematic review and meta-analysis of randomized and nonrandomized controlled weight-loss trials | journal = The American Journal of Clinical Nutrition | volume = 104 | issue = 4 | pages = 1151–1159 | date = October 2016 | pmid = 27604772 | doi = 10.3945/ajcn.116.136879 | doi-access = free }}</ref>。

* '''懷孕''' — 懷孕期間的維他命D含量低跟[[妊娠糖尿病|妊娠糖尿病]]、[[妊娠毒血症|妊娠毒血症]]和細小嬰兒（胎齡）有關<ref name=Agh2013>{{cite journal | vauthors = Aghajafari F, Nagulesapillai T, Ronksley PE, Tough SC, O'Beirne M, Rabi DM | title = Association between maternal serum 25-hydroxyvitamin D level and pregnancy and neonatal outcomes: systematic review and meta-analysis of observational studies | journal = BMJ | volume = 346 | issue =  | pages = f1169 | date = March 2013 | pmid = 23533188 | doi = 10.1136/bmj.f1169 | doi-access = free }}</ref>。儘管孕婦在懷孕期間服用維他命D原則上會增加足月母親的維他命D的血液水平<ref name="palacios">{{cite journal | vauthors = Palacios C, De-Regil LM, Lombardo LK, Peña-Rosas JP | title = Vitamin D supplementation during pregnancy: Updated meta-analysis on maternal outcomes | journal = The Journal of Steroid Biochemistry and Molecular Biology | volume = 164 | pages = 148–155 | date = November 2016 | pmid = 26877200 | pmc = 5357731 | doi = 10.1016/j.jsbmb.2016.02.008 }}</ref>，但對於懷孕母親或嬰兒的全部益處尚未清楚<ref name=Agh2013/><ref name=palacios/><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Roth DE, Leung M, Mesfin E, Qamar H, Watterworth J, Papp E | title = Vitamin D supplementation during pregnancy: state of the evidence from a systematic review of randomised trials | journal = BMJ | volume = 359 | pages = j5237 | date = November 2017 | pmid = 29187358 | pmc = 5706533 | doi = 10.1136/bmj.j5237 }}</ref>。孕婦在妊娠期間攝取足夠的維他命D可能會降低[[妊娠毒血症|子癇前症]]<ref name="Palacios_2019">{{cite journal | vauthors = Palacios C, Kostiuk LK, Peña-Rosas JP | title = Vitamin D supplementation for women during pregnancy | journal = The Cochrane Database of Systematic Reviews | volume = 7 | pages = CD008873 | date = July 2019 | pmid = 31348529 | pmc = 3747784 | doi = 10.1002/14651858.CD008873.pub4 }}</ref>及積極免疫效果<ref name="Wagner_2012">{{cite journal | vauthors = Wagner CL, Taylor SN, Dawodu A, Johnson DD, Hollis BW | title = Vitamin D and its role during pregnancy in attaining optimal health of mother and fetus | journal = Nutrients | volume = 4 | issue = 3 | pages = 208–30 | date = March 2012 | pmid = 22666547 | pmc = 3347028 | doi = 10.3390/nu4030208 }}</ref>的風險。維他命D補充劑還可能降低妊娠糖尿病、體型過小的嬰兒<ref name="Palacios_2019" />以及其生長速度不良的風險<ref name="Bi_2018">{{cite journal | vauthors = Bi WG, Nuyt AM, Weiler H, Leduc L, Santamaria C, Wei SQ | title = Association Between Vitamin D Supplementation During Pregnancy and Offspring Growth, Morbidity, and Mortality: A Systematic Review and Meta-analysis | journal = JAMA Pediatrics | volume = 172 | issue = 7 | pages = 635–645 | date = July 2018 | pmid = 29813153 | pmc = 6137512 | doi = 10.1001/jamapediatrics.2018.0302 }}</ref>。孕婦通常不會服用維他命D的建議用量<ref name="Wagner_2012"/>。

